<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1315,1664]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1315,1340]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[281,422,1316,1340]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypenistis">
<emphasis box="[281,422,1316,1340]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">L. hypenistis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Holloway, 1985" authorityName="Holloway" authorityYear="1985" box="[551,878,1316,1340]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="partitistis">
<emphasis box="[551,688,1317,1340]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">L. partitistis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway" box="[697,878,1316,1340]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refString="Holloway, J. D. (1985) Moths of Borneo, part 14: Family Noctuidae: Subfamilies Euteliinae, Stictopterinae, Plusiinae, Pantheinae. Malayan Nature Journal, 38, 157 - 317." type="journal article" year="1985">
Holloway, 
<number box="[820,878,1316,1340]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by reddish brown color of forewing, while that of 
<taxonomicName box="[441,577,1353,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="partitistis">
<emphasis box="[441,577,1353,1376]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">L. partitistis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is dark greyish-brown; the postmedial line is single, straight, and surrounded with a series of black dots posteriorly, but that of 
<taxonomicName box="[700,837,1389,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="partitistis">
<emphasis box="[700,837,1389,1412]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">L. partitistis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is double and wavy. In the male genitalia, the apex of the uncus is snake-head-shaped, but that of 
<taxonomicName box="[635,771,1425,1448]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="partitistis">
<emphasis box="[635,771,1425,1448]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">L. partitistis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is scrolled apically. In the female genitalia, the lateral lobes are long and nephroid, but that of 
<taxonomicName box="[532,669,1461,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="partitistis">
<emphasis box="[532,669,1461,1484]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">L. partitistis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are short and rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
